0                                   8616      64.              COPY  SLISTMAC
                                    8617             =*******************************************************************
                                    8618             =*                                                                 *
                                    8619             =* Macros for the serialized manipulation of single linked lists   *
                                    8620             =* in memory.  These lists are of the PUSH/POP (LIFO) variety.     *
                                    8621             =* Serialization is achieved using the CDS and CS instructions.    *
                                    8622             =*                                                                 *
                                    8623             =*******************************************************************
0                                   8625             =*******************************************************************
                                    8626             =*                                                                 *
                                    8627             =* Single linked list head fields                                  *
                                    8628             =*                                                                 *
                                    8629             =*******************************************************************
                                    8630             =         MACRO
                                    8631             =&LAB     SHEAD
                                    8632             =         AIF   ('&LAB' EQ '').ERR
                                    8633             =&LAB     DS   0D                   Single linked CDS list
                                    8634             =&LAB.FP  DS    A                   Forward pointer
                                    8635             =&LAB.SEQ DS    A                   CDS sequence number
                                    8636             =         MEXIT
                                    8637             =.ERR     MNOTE 8,'Label (list name) required'
                                    8638             =         MEND
0                                   8640             =*******************************************************************
                                    8641             =*                                                                 *
                                    8642             =* Push an item onto a single linked list                          *
                                    8643             =*                                                                 *
                                    8644             =*******************************************************************
                                    8645             =         MACRO
                                    8646             =&LABEL   SPUSH &HEAD=,&ITEM=
                                    8647             =         LCLC  &X
                                    8648             =         AIF   ('&LABEL' EQ '').NOLAB
                                    8649             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    8650             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    8651             =         AIF   ('&HEAD' EQ '').ERR1
                                    8652             =         AIF   ('&ITEM' EQ '').ERR2
                                    8654             =         LM    R14,R15,&HEAD       Get fwd ptr and sequence number
                                    8655             =         LA    RVR,&ITEM           Point to new item
                                    8656             =         LOOP  BEGIN
                                    8657             =         LA    RS,1(R15)           Increment sequence
                                    8658             =         MVC   &ITEM.(L'&HEAD.FP),&HEAD.FP Set item fwd ptr
                                    8659             =         CDS   R14,RVR,&HEAD       Add item to list
                                    8660             =         UNTIL (Z),END
                                    8662             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    8663             =.ERR1    MNOTE 8,'Head is a required parameter'
                                    8664             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    8665             =.ERR2    MNOTE 8,'Item is a required parameter'
                                    8666             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    8667             =         MEND  ,
0                                   8669             =*******************************************************************
                                    8670             =*                                                                 *
                                    8671             =* Pop an item from a single linked list. Addr returned in RVR     *
1M1SERV   (M1SE00) (09:42) (22MAR04) IHAPSAE  - PSA Extension (ESAME)                                                       Page   50
0Current Usings:  (PZERO,R0)
0Loc    Object Code    Addr1 Addr2  Stmt Lv Lineno    Source Statement           (Hibal 5, Asmedit 3.3)  HLASM R4.0  2004/03/22 09.42
+___    ______ ____    _____ _____  ____ __ ______    ______ _________
0                                   8672             =* (zero if the list was empty).                                   *
                                    8673             =*                                                                 *
                                    8674             =*******************************************************************
                                    8675             =         MACRO
                                    8676             =&LABEL   SPOP  &HEAD=
                                    8677             =         AIF   ('&LABEL' EQ '').NOLAB
                                    8678             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    8679             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    8680             =         AIF   ('&HEAD' EQ '').ERR1
                                    8682             =         LM    RVR,RS,&HEAD        Get fwd and sequence number
                                    8683             =         LOOP  BEGIN
                                    8684             =         IF    (RVR,Z),EXIT        None to get
                                    8685             =         LR    R14,RVR             Point to first item
                                    8686             =         L     R14,0(R14)          Get fwd pointer
                                    8687             =         LA    R15,1(RS)           Increment sequence
                                    8688             =         CDS   RVR,R14,&HEAD       Remove item from list
                                    8689             =         UNTIL (Z),END
                                    8691             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    8692             =.ERR1    MNOTE 8,'Head is a required parameter'
                                    8693             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    8694             =         MEND  ,
0                                   8696             =*******************************************************************
                                    8697             =*                                                                 *
                                    8698             =* Get an available item from list (ptr returned in RVR). Memory   *
                                    8699             =* will be obtained if the list is empty.                          *
                                    8700             =*                                                                 *
                                    8701             =*******************************************************************
                                    8702             =         MACRO
                                    8703             =&LABEL   SAVAIL &HEAD=,&LEN=,&LOC=GLOBHI,&FIX=,&PAGE=
                                    8704             =         AIF   ('&LABEL' EQ '').NOLAB
                                    8705             =&LABEL   LABEL ,
                                    8706             =.NOLAB   ANOP  ,
                                    8707             =         AIF   ('&HEAD' EQ '').ERR1
                                    8708             =         AIF   ('&LEN' EQ '').ERR2
                                    8709             =         SPOP  HEAD=&HEAD          pop a free item
                                    8710             =         IF    (RVR,Z),BEGIN       empty list
                                    8711             =         VMGET &LEN,LOC=&LOC,FIX=&FIX,PAGE=&PAGE
                                    8712             =         IF    ('LTR RVR,RVR',ZERO),'ABORT NO_MEM_&HEAD'
                                    8713             =         END   ,
                                    8714             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    8715             =.ERR1    MNOTE 8,'Head is a required parameter'
                                    8716             =         AGO   .EXIT
                                    8717             =.ERR2    MNOTE 8,'Len is a required parameter'
                                    8718             =.EXIT    ANOP  ,
                                    8719             =         MEND  ,

                                    8810      70.     *     UTRACE -  Mode 1 Trace request                              *
                                    8811      71.     *                                                                 *

0                                   8814      74.              MACRO
                                    8815      75.     &L       UTRACE &CLASS=,&CODE=,&PSW=SCPPSW,&DATA=
                                    8816      76.     .*
                                    8817      77.     .* Mode 1 local session trace
                                    8818      78.     .*
                                    8819      79.              LCLA  &CLSNUM,&DWC,&DWI,&DWL
                                    8820      80.              PSET  @UTRACE,CLEAR=NO
                                    8821      81.     .*
                                    8822      82.     .* Determine trace class
                                    8823      83.     &CLSNUM  SETA  0
                                    8824      84.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'SVC').GOTCLS
                                    8825      85.     &CLSNUM  SETA  1
                                    8826      86.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'PI').GOTCLS
                                    8827      87.     &CLSNUM  SETA  2
                                    8828      88.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'PER').GOTCLS
                                    8829      89.     &CLSNUM  SETA  3
                                    8830      90.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'MON').GOTCLS
                                    8831      91.     &CLSNUM  SETA  4
                                    8832      92.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'IO').GOTCLS
                                    8833      93.     &CLSNUM  SETA  5
                                    8834      94.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'TIMER').GOTCLS
                                    8835      95.     &CLSNUM  SETA  6
                                    8836      96.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'ATTN').GOTCLS
                                    8837      97.     &CLSNUM  SETA  7
                                    8838      98.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'RUNCLP').GOTCLS
                                    8839      99.     &CLSNUM  SETA  8
                                    8840     100.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'RUNUSER').GOTCLS
                                    8841     101.     &CLSNUM  SETA  9
                                    8842     102.              AIF   ('&CLASS' EQ 'UXIT').GOTCLS
                                    8843     103.              MNOTE 8,'INVALID TRACE CLASS'
                                    8844     104.              MEXIT
                                    8845     105.     .GOTCLS  ANOP
                                    8846     106.              MVI   @UTCLASS,&CLSNUM
                                    8847     107.     .*
                                    8848     108.     .* Add sub-class
                                    8849     109.     .*
                                    8850     110.              AIF   (N'&CODE NE 1).NOCODE
                                    8851     111.              PMOV  @UTCODE,&CODE
                                    8852     112.              AGO   .CODEOK
                                    8853     113.     .NOCODE  ANOP
                                    8854     114.              CLEAR @UTCODE
                                    8855     115.     .CODEOK  ANOP
                                    8856     116.     .*
                                    8857     117.     .* Add current PSW
                                    8858     118.     .*
                                    8859     119.              AIF   (N'&PSW NE 1).NOPSW
                                    8860     120.              PMOV  @UTPSW,&PSW
                                    8861     121.              AGO   .PSWOK

0                                   8862     122.     .NOPSW   ANOP
                                    8863     123.              CLEAR @UTPSW
                                    8864     124.     .PSWOK   ANOP
                                    8865     125.     .*
                                    8866     126.     .* Add the data words
                                    8867     127.     .*
                                    8868     128.     &DWC     SETA  0
                                    8869     129.     &DWI     SETA  N'&DATA
                                    8870     130.     .DATLOOP AIF   (&DWC EQ &DWI).DATEND
                                    8871     131.     &DWL     SETA  &DWC*4
                                    8872     132.              MVC   @UTDATA+&DWL.(4),&DATA(&DWC+1)
                                    8873     133.     &DWC     SETA  &DWC+1
                                    8874     134.              AGO   .DATLOOP
                                    8875     135.     .DATEND  ANOP
                                    8876     136.     .*
                                    8877     137.     .* Set the number of data words
                                    8878     138.     .*
                                    8879     139.              MVI   @UTDWC,&DWC
                                    8880     140.     .*
                                    8881     141.     .* Call the trace routine
                                    8882     142.     .*
                                    8883     143.              ACALL  UTRACE
                                    8884     144.              MEND

 00000C 00                          9468  1          =SSBFLAG    FLAG  ,                   Flags
 00000D                             9472  1          =           DS    XL3
 000010                             9473  1          =SSBNAME    DS    CL200               Symbol name
 0000D8                000D8 000D8  9474             =         END

-                                   9484     223.              COPY  SSAB
                                    9485=            =
                                    9486=            =                                                                     
                                    9487=            =    SSAB --   Shared Symbol Access Block                             
                                    9488=            =                                                                     
                                    9489=            =              This control block represents the access of a user to  
                                    9490=            =              shared symbols.  There is one for each SPB which       
                                    9491=            =              contains shared symbols referenced by this user.       
                                    9492=            =                                                                     
                                    9493=            =              When a search for symbols is done, the SPB's in this  ed
                                    9494=            =              list are searched first.  This will ensure that the    
                                    9495=            =              program gets a consistent set of symbols.  Each        
                                    9496=            =              instance of this control block implies a reference     
                                    9497=            =              count in the SPB that this points to.                  
                                    9498=            =                                                                     
                                                      
0000000                00000 0000C  9499             =SSAB     RECORD BEGIN
 000000                             9507  1          =SSABID     DS    CL4'SSAB'
 000004                             9508  1          =SSABNEXT   DS    A             Next SSAB ptr (or zero)
 000008                             9509  1          =SSABSPB    DS    A             Address of the SPB this refers to
 00000C                0000C 0000C  9510             =         END
-                                   9520     225.     *
 000000                00000 000D0  9521     226.     @SSWA    RECORD BEGIN
 000000                             9529  1  227.     @SSNAME    DS    CL(L'SSBNAME)       Working SSB name
 0000C8                             9530  1  228.     @SSWORD    DS    A                   Return value
 0000CC                             9531  1  229.     @SSRV      DS    F                   Return code
 0000D0                000D0 000D0  9532     230.              END

                                   38927    5564.                If we haven't found it yet, then we go through the valid

                                   38929    5566.                The overhead should be minimal, since normally symbols will   
                                   38930    5567.                all come from one or two SPB's which have already been        
                                   38931    5568.                referenced. If we find it at this point, we must also insert

0                                  39201    5604.     
                                   39202    5605.             PURSPB -- This routine purges the program described in the   
                                   39203    5606.                       SPB passed if possible.  It frees the memory and   
                                   39204    5607.                       returns the SPB to its initial state, removing     
                                   39205    5608.                       any shared symbols the program defined.  This may  
                                   39206    5609.                       only be done if all the following conditions are   
                                   39207    5610.                       met:                                               
                                   39208    5611.                                                                          
                                   39209    5612.                       1) The program is either purgeable or is a         
                                   39210    5613.                          corpse.                                         
                                   39211    5614.                                                                          
                                   39212    5615.                       2) There are no current users of the program       
                                   39213    5616.                                                                          
                                   39214    5617.                                                                          
                                   39215    5618.                       3) There are no users referring to shared symbols  
                                   39216    5619.                          of the program.                                 
                                   39217    5620.                                                                          
                                   39218    5621.                       4) The program had not already been purged.        
                                   39219    5622.                                                                          
                                   39220    5623.                   On Entry:                                              
                                   39221    5624.                       R1 -- Address of the SPB                           
                                   39222    5625.
